# Why: Email footer is the most-visible Documenso brand surface — every
#      signing-invite email shows it, every reminder, every completion
#      notice. Three changes:
#
#        1. "Powered by Documenso" link → "Powered by Pacta", with the URL
#           pointing to bizrethink.ai instead of documen.so/mail-footer.
#        2. Link color flips from Documenso's `#7AC455` (green) to charcoal
#           `#1f2937` matching Pacta's neutral palette (per the brand
#           decisions locked in the rebrand plan).
#        3. Address fallback (when an org has brandingEnabled=false or no
#           brandingCompanyDetails set): "Documenso, Inc. / 2261 Market
#           Street, San Francisco, CA" → "BizRethink AI (Server Baba Inc.) /
#           Florida, USA".
#
#      The Pacta product name and parent brand are read from APP_NAME and
#      APP_PARENT_BRAND constants in packages/lib/constants/app.ts (added
#      via overlay 021), so future renames are a one-file change.
#
#      What stays unchanged: the brandingEnabled / brandingHidePoweredBy
#      gating logic. Tenants that set their own `brandingCompanyDetails` see
#      THEIR address; tenants that haven't yet (or use platform default) see
#      the BizRethink fallback above.
#
#      Fragility: LOW. Footer template gets ~1 commit per quarter upstream.
#      Imports at the top will conflict if upstream adds new imports; trivial
#      to resolve. The Trans/JSX block is stable.
#
diff --git a/packages/email/template-components/template-footer.tsx b/packages/email/template-components/template-footer.tsx
--- a/packages/email/template-components/template-footer.tsx
+++ b/packages/email/template-components/template-footer.tsx
# (full file diff — see commit)
